title: For Sale:   SOLD!!! S&W NO DASH! Model 19 Nickel Finish .357 Magnum 4"
postcontent:
SOLD will delete soon!

Up for sale is a very, very nice shooting S&W No dash Model 19 with a nickel finish. In mint condition these go for $1k +. This no dash model 19 would be an excellent candidate to be sent to S&W for restoration ($350 I believe). This gun is used and was a police sidearm. The finish has lots of light swirls that could be polished out. They are only visible up close. The finish looks beautiful from 6 inches away. But there are some light scratches on the side plate over the S&W logo where the holster snap was. They are light and do not go all the way through the nickel. I will add that picture later since I cant find it in my files.

The trigger is perfection. Smooth double action and the trigger goes off if you look at it in single action. No cylinder fore/aft play and very good lockup. The bore is excellent.

I buy/sell/trade guns all the time as a way to try as many as I can. I'm not interested in revolvers at all but I have held onto this for longer than any handgun I have purchased in the last two years. This thing is awesome and I have never been more accurate with any other pistol. I planned that if I kept it until next year I would send it in for restoration and keep it forever. 

I never believed it but there is something special about these classic S&W revolvers. the trigger is smooth, the fit and finish is amazing you can really feel the difference in quality than in modern semi autos. I wish you could get this kind of soul in a semi auto.

I do not need to sell, I have had a few unexpected technology items break and need replacing so the "toy" fund is low so I'm selling this excellent pistol.

Price is $600 OBO cash preferred but I will consider some trades. No other revolvers!!!

All FOID laws apply, You will send me a scan of your DL & FOID so I can have the paperwork ready.

The smallest dot Trijicon offers in this model is 7 MOA, that means it covers 7 inches at 100 yards, 14 inches at 200yds, 21 inches at 300, etc...  You put the triangle at the top of center mass and you have a "kill shot" from 0-300yds. 

The base that comes with this RMR is the Trijicon low profile picatinny mount. I still have the original Trijicon carrying case and all the paperwork. The price is firm. Try finding a better price anywhere.

Description: CLT DEFENDER COMPACT 45 3SS 7R 
 Manufacturer: Colt 
 Model #: Defender

 Stock: Rubber Grips, Finger Grooves 
 Sights: White Dot Carry Sights 
 Barrel Length: 3" 
 Overall Length: 6 3/4" 
 Weight: 22 1/2 oz 
 Caliber: 45AP 
 Capacity: 7+1 
 Action: Single Action 
 # of Mags: 2 
 Features: Adjustable Aluminum Trigger, Combat Hammer 
 Product Review 
Reviewed By:  08/09/2013 Rating: 5 of 5 Stars! [5 of 5 Stars!] 
I have previously owned a Colt Defender and a Colt Night defender and they were both excellent pistols but got traded somewhere down the line. So I was eager to have another and jumped on it when one became available again.
I am basically a Kimber guy and really love their pistols and own several, they are tight, accurate and sometimes tempermental. On the other hand the several Colts that I have owned rattle when you shake them, sometimes are not finished well and may seem dated. But more importantly they have always been reliable, shot every time I pulled the trigger and have always been accurate. I have never doubted that a Colt would not come through for me if I ever needed it to. This Defender is no different. I have only had it two days but have put 300 mixed rounds through it with absolutely no problems. For me the 3" 1911's are the perfect carry pistols and are very accurate to 25 yards and further with practice. This Defender has a great finish, looks good and feels good in my hand and loaded is light enough for all day carry. Even with it's light weight, recovery shots are just as quick as with my Kimber Super Carry Ultra HD which is much heavier with its steel frame.
All said if you are looking for a reliable 3" 1911, you really can't go wrong with the Colt Defender and it's proven history.
